ttribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Conyers married Robert Conyers before 1185, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1180–Female":"1180–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","before 1185":"enne 1185","1180":"1180","England":"England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1180–Female":"1180–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","before 1185":"ennen vuotta 1185","1180":"1180","England":"England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","–Male":"Décédé","1180–Female":"1180–Décédée","–Female":"Décédée","before 1185":"avant 1185","1180":"1180","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Conyers a épousé Robert Conyers avant 1185, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","1180–Female":"1180–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","before 1185":"vor 1185","1180":"1180","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Mrs Robert Conyers hat vor 1185 in England Robert Conyers geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","–Male":"Desede","1180–Female":"1180–D